---
const points = [
  {
    tag: 'exit 1',
    title: 'Drift-failing validators',
    body: 'Overlay-drift, contract-manifest, task-shape, and hook-guardrail checks that exit non-zero the moment policy drifts. Wire them into CI and the build breaks on violation.',
  },
  {
    tag: 'sha-256',
    title: 'Self-verifying generated code',
    body: 'Every generated validator carries a hash of its own rendered source. The harness refuses to run a check that has been hand-edited — no silently trusting drifted policy.',
  },
  {
    tag: 'sandboxed',
    title: 'Hard safety boundaries',
    body: 'Symlink-resolving path safety, traversal and .git rejection, and injection-as-data rendering — a hostile project.name is escaped, never executed. All backed by adversarial tests.',
  },
  {
    tag: 'pre-import',
    title: 'Harness ≠ runner, enforced',
    body: 'Codex hooks are scanned for banned mutation tokens before they are imported. The boundary between shaping work and executing it is mechanical, not a promise in a README.',
  },
];
---
<section class="wedge" id="how">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="head" data-reveal>
      <p class="eyebrow">The wedge</p>
      <h2>Most tools stop at organizing prompts.<br /><span class="muted">Structor enforces them.</span></h2>
      <p class="lede">
        Reliable agentic engineering needs context architecture <em>plus</em> mechanical
        enforcement. The generated harness ships with checks that fail the build when the
        rules and the code fall out of sync.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="grid">
      {points.map((p) => (
        <article class="card" data-reveal>
          <span class="card-tag">{p.tag}</span>
          <h3>{p.title}</h3>
          <p>{p.body}</p>
        </article>
      ))}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .wedge {
    padding: 5rem 0;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
  }

  .head { margin-bottom: 3rem; max-width: 760px; }
  .eyebrow { margin-bottom: 1.1rem; }

  h2 {
    font-size: clamp(1.6rem, 3.2vw, 2.25rem);
    font-weight: 740;
    line-height: 1.15;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
  }
  h2 .muted { color: var(--text-muted); }

  .lede {
    margin-top: 1.1rem;
    font-size: 1.0625rem;
    line-height: 1.65;
    color: var(--text);
    max-width: 60ch;
  }
  .lede em { color: var(--text-strong); font-style: normal; font-weight: 600; }

  .grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(248px, 1fr));
    gap: 1rem;
  }

  .card {
    position: relative;
    background: linear-gradient(180deg, var(--surface), var(--bg-elev));
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: var(--radius);
    padding: 1.6rem 1.5rem 1.7rem;
    overflow: hidden;
    transition: border-color 0.2s ease, transform 0.2s ease;
  }
  .card::before {
    content: "";
    position: absolute;
    top: 0; left: 0; right: 0;
    height: 1px;
    background: linear-gradient(90deg, transparent, var(--accent-line), transparent);
    opacity: 0;
    transition: opacity 0.25s ease;
  }
  .card:hover {
    border-color: var(--border-strong);
    transform: translateY(-3px);
  }
  .card:hover::before { opacity: 1; }

  .card-tag {
    display: inline-block;
    font-family: var(--mono);
    font-size: 0.7rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.04em;
    color: var(--accent-bright);
    background: var(--accent-soft);
    border: 1px solid var(--accent-line);
    padding: 0.15rem 0.5rem;
    border-radius: 5px;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .card h3 {
    font-size: 1.0625rem;
    font-weight: 680;
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
    margin-bottom: 0.6rem;
  }
  .card p {
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    line-height: 1.62;
    color: var(--text-muted);
  }
</style>
